verses.text_plain: What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that grace may abound?
verses.verse_html: 1What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that grace may abound?

verses.text_plain: God forbid. How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein?
verses.verse_html: 2God forbid. How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein?

verses.text_plain: Know ye not, that so many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?
verses.verse_html: 3Know ye not, that so many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?

verses.text_plain: Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death: that like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.
verses.verse_html: 4Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death: that like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.

verses.text_plain: For if we have been planted together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also in the likeness of his resurrection:
verses.verse_html: 5For if we have been planted together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also in the likeness of his resurrection:

verses.text_plain: Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should not serve sin.
verses.verse_html: 6Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should not serve sin.

verses.text_plain: For he that is dead is freed from sin.
verses.verse_html: 7For he that is dead is freed from sin.

verses.text_plain: Now if we be dead with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him:
verses.verse_html: 8Now if we be dead with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him:

verses.text_plain: Knowing that Christ being raised from the dead dieth no more; death hath no more dominion over him.
verses.verse_html: 9Knowing that Christ being raised from the dead dieth no more; death hath no more dominion over him.

verses.text_plain: For in that he died, he died unto sin once: but in that he liveth, he liveth unto God.
verses.verse_html: 10For in that he died, he died unto sin once: but in that he liveth, he liveth unto God.

verses.text_plain: Likewise reckon ye also yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord.
verses.verse_html: 11Likewise reckon ye also yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord.

verses.text_plain: Let not sin therefore reign in your mortal body, that ye should obey it in the lusts thereof.
verses.verse_html: 12 Let not sin therefore reign in your mortal body, that ye should obey it in the lusts thereof.

verses.text_plain: Neither yield ye your members as instruments of unrighteousness unto sin: but yield yourselves unto God, as those that are alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness unto God.
verses.verse_html: 13Neither yield ye your members as instruments of unrighteousness unto sin: but yield yourselves unto God, as those that are alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness unto God.

verses.text_plain: For sin shall not have dominion over you: for ye are not under the law, but under grace.
verses.verse_html: 14For sin shall not have dominion over you: for ye are not under the law, but under grace.

verses.text_plain: What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? God forbid.
verses.verse_html: 15What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? God forbid.

verses.text_plain: Know ye not, that to whom ye yield yourselves servants to obey, his servants ye are to whom ye obey; whether of sin unto death, or of obedience unto righteousness?
verses.verse_html: 16Know ye not, that to whom ye yield yourselves servants to obey, his servants ye are to whom ye obey; whether of sin unto death, or of obedience unto righteousness?

verses.text_plain: But God be thanked, that ye were the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered you.
verses.verse_html: 17But God be thanked, that ye were the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered you.

verses.text_plain: Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 18Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness.

verses.text_plain: I speak after the manner of men because of the infirmity of your flesh: for as ye have yielded your members servants to uncleanness and to iniquity unto iniquity; even so now yield your members servants to righteousness unto holiness.
verses.verse_html: 19I speak after the manner of men because of the infirmity of your flesh: for as ye have yielded your members servants to uncleanness and to iniquity unto iniquity; even so now yield your members servants to righteousness unto holiness.

verses.text_plain: For when ye were the servants of sin, ye were free from righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 20For when ye were the servants of sin, ye were free from righteousness.

verses.text_plain: What fruit had ye then in those things whereof ye are now ashamed? for the end of those things is death.
verses.verse_html: 21What fruit had ye then in those things whereof ye are now ashamed? for the end of those things is death.

verses.text_plain: But now being made free from sin, and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness, and the end everlasting life.
verses.verse_html: 22But now being made free from sin, and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness, and the end everlasting life.

verses.text_plain: For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
verses.verse_html: 23For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
